Development of TALYS since release of TALYS-2.2

- December 18, 2025

********** Release of TALYS-2.2 **********

- February 10 2026

Solved a bug for microscopic alpha OMPs, ecisstep should be defaulted 
to a value of 0.1, just like for JLM

- March 10 2026

Added a keyword globaldisp, by default set to 'n', to use a global
dispersive OMP for neutrons. results are not good yet.

- March 24 2026

Included PSF model for strength 11. This can be spin and 
parity dependent and for that the keyword strengthjp was introduced.

- March 25 2026

Added an option to use the real Fermi energy for the global optical 
model. So far, only the systematics formula from KD03 paper was used,
but this may give problems for exotic nuclides. With the keyword 
globalfermi y the Fermi energy is calculated from the real 
separation energies from the mass table.

- March 26 2026

Reduced the beta2,3,4 deformation parameters in deformpar.f90 by 50%.
For many exotic nuclides, taking the plain systematic formula give 
direct inelastic cross sections whose sum is larger than the reaction 
cross section. We build in security by multiplying the beta's by 0.3.

- April 2 2026

Corrected the output of D0 in level density tables which is in eV and 
not in keV. Problem found by Sandor Kovacs.

- April 2 2026

Solved an error found by Alexandre Konobeyev. Results were different
depending on whether filedensity was set to n or y. It turned out
that without output of level densities the value of Ncum was not 
initialized, and thus zero. This affects the correction for missing
levels when calculating discrete levels versus continuum cross sections.

- April 29 2026

Changed the default of soswitch from 3. to 20. Too large discontinuities 
for the total cross sections for rotation nuclei were observed.

- May 6 2026

Changed numlev2 from 200 to 300 to get resonating (alpha,n) cross sections
with 'pseudoresonances y'

- May 9 2026

Added keywords Emaxpseudores, pseudoreswidth, pseudoresfade to adjust the
contribution from resonance reactions.

- July 12 2026

Robert found an error with the Ufermi boundary, solved in checkvalues.f90
